title: About
text:
Python Code Example
We generate a simple plot using Python and matplotlib to showcase our data visualization:


import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

x=[1,2,3]
y=[2,4,6]

plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
plt.plot(x, y, label="Simple Plot", color="blue")
plt.title("Simple Plot for 5000")
plt.xlabel("X") #depend on topic
plt.ylabel("Y") #depend on topic
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()

I have three bestfriends in a house since 2020. They are dogs!! They are all super active, sweet, and fluffy. Consist of one husky mixed and two pure boxers (they are twin).
